M||tx|---
M||titl|Minimize Serialization at RSC Boundaries
M||impa|hi
M||impa|reduces data transfer size
M||tags|server, rsc, serialization, props
M||tx|---
M|Mini|tx|The rc Server/Client boundary serializes all object properties into strings and embeds them in the HTML rp and subsequent RSC requests. This serialized data directly impacts page weight and load time, so **size matters a lot**. Only pass fields that the client actually uses.
M|Mini|**In|**
M|Mini|tx|```tsx
M|Mini|tx|async fn Page() {
M|Mini|tx|const us = await fetchUser()  // 50 fields
M|Mini|tx|return <Profile us={us} />
M|Mini|tx|}
M|Mini|tx|'use client'
M|Mini|func|{ us: us }) {
M|Mini|tx|return <div>{us.name}</div>  // uses 1 field
M|Mini|tx|}
M|Mini|tx|```
M|Mini|**Co|**
M|Mini|tx|```tsx
M|Mini|tx|async fn Page() {
M|Mini|tx|const us = await fetchUser()
M|Mini|tx|return <Profile name={us.name} />
M|Mini|tx|}
M|Mini|tx|'use client'
M|Mini|func|{ name: string }) {
M|Mini|tx|return <div>{name}</div>
M|Mini|tx|}
M|Mini|tx|```